It should!
```
    if (systemAnimationsEnabled || getRepeatCount() == 0) {
      animator.playAnimation();
    }
```
So if `systemAnimationsEnabled` is false and as `getRepeatCount()` return `-1` (https://developer.android.com/reference/android/animation/ValueAnimator.html#INFINITE), there is no `animator.playAnimation()`

However, we rarely experienced a looping animation on one of our lottie during our tests even when `systemAnimationsEnabled` == `false`, but we don't know why for now.
